Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: On descending the range, we entered a valley of considerable extent, to the left of which was a native settlement. The inhabitants having, a short time previously, left for Paupo, we found no one there but an old woman, who luckily had a good supply of corn and potatoes, and in whose hut I managed to sleep very comfortably.
